OL,6,FThe disease can also lead to further
OL,7,Fcomplications such as oesophageal
OL,8,Fulcers, a scarred and narrow
OL,9,Foesophagus, Barrett's oesophagus `
OL,10,Fchanges to the cells in the lining of
OL,11,Fthe oesophagus ` and oesophageal
OL,12,Fcancer.
OL,14,FIt is estimated that one in every 10
OL,15,Fto 20 people with Barrett's oesophagus
OL,16,Fwill develop oesophageal cancer within
OL,17,F10 to 20 years.
OL,19,FDanielle Harding, 30, recently became
OL,20,Fthe first patient with GORD to undergo
OL,21,Fthe procedure at UHS.
