OL,3,CFirst patient fitted with new device
OL,4,Cpreventing acid reflux
OL,6,FMs Harding was prescribed medication
OL,7,Ffrom her GP which initially stopped
OL,8,Fthe symptoms only for them to return.
OL,10,FAn endoscopy showed that she had
OL,11,Fsignificant damage to her oesophagus
OL,12,Fand that she would need to remain on a
OL,13,Fhigh dose of medication for life.
OL,15,FMs Harding said: "I had the surgery a
OL,16,Flittle over a month ago and my
OL,17,Fsymptoms have completely disappeared.
OL,18,FI'm absolutely delighted and am so
OL,19,Fgrateful to Fergus and the team at
OL,20,FUHS, it has changed my life."
